==History==
Matsushima-Kaigan Station opened on April 18, 1927 as {{nihongo|'''Matsushima K<U+014D>en Station'''|<U+677E><U+5CF6><U+516C><U+5712><U+99C5>||}} on the Miyagi Electric Railway. The line was nationalized on May 1, 1944 and the station was renamed to its present name at that time. The station was absorbed into the JR East network upon the [[privatization]] of [[JNR]] on April 1, 1987. The station was closed from March 11 to May 28, 2011 due to damage associated with the [[2011 T<U+014D>hoku earthquake and tsunami]].

